
[1]clarify

   CLARIFY, v.t.

   1. To make clear; to purify from feculent matter; to defecate; to fine;
   applied particularly to liquors; as, to clarify wine, or syrup.

   2. To make clear; to brighten or illuminate; applied to the mind or
   reason.

                                CLARIFY, v.i.

   1. To clear up; to grow clear or bright.

   His understanding clarifies, in discoursing with another.

   2. To grow or become clear or fine; to become pure, as liquors. Cider
   clarifies by fermentation.
